<body>
<p>第一章：动词时态</p>
<div>
	<ul style="list-style-type: cjk-ideographic">
		<li>
			一般现在时
			<ul style="list-style-type: decimal">
				<li>
					用于表示"真理，客观存在和习惯"等概念等句子中
					<p>Light travels more quickly than sounds.</p>
				</li>
				<li>
					在表示时间、条件、方式、让步等的状语从句中，用一般进行时表示将来概念。
					<p>Whatever you say I won't change my mind.</p>
				</li>
				
				<li>用在make sure(certain),see(to it),I hope,I bet,I suppose和assume等词后面的that分句中表示将来。</li>
				<p>I bet he comes back tomorrow.</p>
				<li>
					瞬间动词的一般现在时可用来表示将来。这类动词包括：ask，arrive，begin，buy，come，decide，go，hear，leave，lose，meet，recover，return，sail，see，stop，talk，visit等。
					<p>She leaves Beijing for HongKong next week.</p>
					<p>注：瞬间动词的一般现在时用在由the moment, the minute, the morning ,the day, the year, instantly , immediately, directly 等词引导等时间状语分句中表将来。</p>
				</li>
			</ul>
		</li>
		<li>
			一般过去时
			<ul style="list-style-type: decimal">
				<li>
					表示在过去某一时刻或某一时间段里经常或反复发生等动作，常与表示过去的时间状语连用。
					<p>Early in the morning , he woke up ,jumped out of bed , washed and hurried to the worksite.</p>
				</li>
				<li>
					在表示时间、原因、条件从句中代替过去将来时
					<p>He said he woldn't go with us if it rained.</p>
				</li>
				<li>
					用在It's time that ……,I wish that ……,I'd rather that …… ,If only ……等结构的后面表示现在或者未来的臆想情况或非真实情况
					<p>It's time that we took a rest.</p>
				</li>
			</ul>
		</li>
		<li>
			将来时（一般将来时，过去将来时）
			<ul style="list-style-type: decimal">
				<li>
					be going to,be about to,be to + 不定式表示将来（其中：be to 不定式表按计划安排发生的事情）
					<p>I felt that something terrible was about to happen.</p>
				</li>
				<li>
					瞬间动词中，表示位移或者起始的动词，如 arrive , come , die , drive , fly , go ,give , leave , meet ,play , publish ,return , start ,sail 等的进行时也表示将来的动作。
					<p>
						Our dean is giving a report this afternoon.
					</p>
				</li>
				<li>
					某些瞬间动词的一般式也可表示将来的动作。
				</li>
				<li>
					过去将来式常用于间接引语中。
					<p>He told the enemies that they would never get everything from him.</p>
				</li>
			</ul>
		</li>
		<li>
			进行时（过去进行时，现在进行时，将来进行时）
			<ul style="list-style-type: circle">
				<li>
					现在进行时和过去进行时。
					<ul style="list-style-type: decimal">
						<li>
							进行时常与 always , constantly , continually , forever , perpetually 等副词连用，表示赞扬或者厌恶等感情。
							<p>You are continually finding fault with us.</p>
						</li>
						<li>
							表示现阶段或者过去某阶段正在进行而此时此刻不一定在进行的动作，因此可以和these day, at that time等时间状语连用
							<p>They were building a dam last winter.</p>
						</li>
						<li>
							现在进行时和过去进行时还可以替代时间，条件状语，以及某些宾语从句中的将来时。
							<p>I was afraid it was going to rain.</p>
						</li>
						<li>
							动词 cost ,resemble 用于进行体，有时有" 越来越……"的意思。
							<p>Apples are costing more these days.</p>
						</li>
					</ul>
				</li>
				<li>
					将来进行时。
					<p>用will/shall + 不定式进行体表示将来时间，一般只用作动作的动词，不能用于状态动词，除有表示将来某一时刻进行的动作外，还可表示预料将要发生的的动作事实，要注意它和一般将来时（只表示未来的意图）的区别</p>
					<p>I shall go to the station.(express intention)</p>
				</li>
				<li>
					不能用于进行时态的几种情况。
					<ul style="list-style-type: decimal">
						<li>
							be able to 与 have to 都不能用作进行体.
							<p>If the volume of British investment is to be increased ,other demands on national resources have to be reduce or eliminated.</p>
						</li>
						
						<li>
							不能用作进行体的动词.
							<ul style="list-style-type: lower-alpha">
								<li>
									思维动词(verbs of thinking)如：think , know , realize , remember , mean , understand , believe等
									<p>I think we have met before.</p>
								</li>
								<li>
									某些情感动词(verbs of emotion)如:like , dislike ,wish ,want ,desire,love,hate,forgive,refuse等不用做进行时态
									<p>I love you.</p>
								</li>
								<li>
									感官动词（verbs of senses），如see,notice ，recognize ,hear 等不用于现在进行时。
									<p>I saw a boy kicking a ball in the street.</p>
								</li>
								<li>
									含有"具有，归属"等意义的动词如：have , own , possess , belong to等
									<p>This book belongs to me.</p>
								</li>
								<li>
									其他不能用于进行体的动词还有：master , seem , look ,appear ,consist of等。
									<p>Your age doesn't matter.</p>
								</li>
							</ul>
						</li>
					</ul>
				</li>
			</ul>
		</li>
		<li>
			完成时（现在完成时，过去完成时，将来完成时)
			<ul>
				<li>
					现在完成时
					<p>现在完成时通常表示：已完成的动作；过去的动作对现在的影响；过去的经验；过去的动作一直持续到现在。跟现在完成时连用的时间状语通常是：just ， since ，already，yet，ever（到现在位置任何时候），never，lately，recently，the last few days，several times，so far，the moment，up to now，up to the present，all day（morning etc.），as soon as ，when ，util等。</p>
					<p>It has rained every day so far this month. </p>
					<p>[注]在含有 as soon as , the moment , until ,when 等引导等时间状语里，如果主句谓语动词用将来时，从句谓语动词可用现在完成时表示将来概念。</p>
					<p>I'll contact you the moment I have obtained the document.</p>
					<ul style="list-style-type: disc">
						<li>
							在下面这些结构中要用完成体。这些结构包括：This (That / It)is the first(second/third),This is the only,This is the much the best (finest/worst/most interesting)
							<p>It is a fantastic landscape that we have seen.</p>
						</li>
						<li>
							关于since的几种用法。
							<ul style="list-style-type: circle">
								<li>
									现在完成时与since引导的时间状语从句连用时，从句动词要用一般过去时，主句动词用现在完成时。
									<p>I have covered 80 pages since you lent me the book.</p>
								</li>
								<li>
									since 引导的分句也可用完成时，表示分局的动作或状态持续至今。
									<p>They haven't had a good rest since they have had a baby.</p>
								</li>
							</ul>
						</li>
						<li>
							瞬间动词的完成体。
							<ul style="list-style-type: circle">
								<li>瞬间动词用语完成体时，其肯定式不能和时间段状语连用，即不能和表示一段时间的短语连用，如in the past,last few days, for three days, by/till/up to now, since , so far等
									<p>Their daughter was born three years ago.</p>
								</li>
								<li>
									瞬间动词的否定式可以和时间段状语连用，构成完成体。
									<p>We haven't seen each other for over 2 years.</p>
								</li>
							</ul>
						</li>
					</ul>
				</li>
				<li>
					过去完成时
					<p>过去完成时是指过去某一时段之前已经完成的动作，是相对于过去某一时刻而言，它一定要与确切的表示过去的时间状语并用，进行比较。</p>
					<ul style="list-style-type: decimal">
						<li>在由when，before，after，until，as soon as等引导的时间状语从句，以及与by链接的时间状语连用时，如果主句谓语从句与谓语都表示过去的动作，那么动作在先的谓语
							<p>As soon as the sun had set we returned to our hotel.</p>
						</li>
						<li>
							在含有hardly/scarcely...when , no sooner ...than 等结构的主句复合句中，主句谓语 动词用过去完成时，从句谓语动词用一般过去时。
							<p>He had no sooner arrived there than he fell ill.</p>
							
						</li>
						<li>
							had hoped/intended/planned/thought/meant/supposed/expected + 不定式/that 从句（从句谓语动词常用would + 动词原形）表示过去未曾实现的希望打算或者意图。
							<p>He had intended to come yesterday.</p>
						</li>
					</ul>
				</li>
				<li>将来完成时
					<ul style="list-style-type: decimal">
						<li>将来完成时也必须与一个表示未来确切的某一时间点进行比较，也可表示一个动作在另一个未来动作之前已完成。
							<p>On her next anniversary she will have been married for 25 years.</p>
						</li>
						<li>by the time ,by the end of ,before 常用来引导将来完成时。
							<p>By the end of this year, I shall have been almost everywhere.</p>
						</li>
						<li>过去将来完成时常用语间接引语中。
						<p>
							Betty said that she would have arrived there by that night .
						</p></li>
					</ul>
				</li>
				<li>完成进行时
					<p>现在完成进行时强调一个动作延续到说话时刚结束，或者表示说话的时候动作仍在进展中。过去完成进行时则表示动作延续到过去某一时间点前刚刚结束，或者表示动作到过去某一时间点还在继续进展中。</p>
					<p>She had been working at her report when I went to see her.</p>
					<p>The giant lady with torche has been welcoming people from many countries for a hundred years.</p>
					<ul style="list-style-type: disc">
						<li>how long 习惯上引导现在完成进行时
						<p>
							How long have you been studying English ?
						</p>
							<p>
								How long have they been digging the ditch?
							</p>
						</li>
						<li>
							以how long 询问时，动词know，love，hate，belong to等不能用现在完成进行时，只能用现在完成时。
							<p>
								How long have you known him ?
							</p>
						</li>
					</ul>
				</li>
			</ul>
		</li>
	</ul>
</div>
